entries.meaning: A publication, such as a newspaper or magazine, that is issued with a printed date later than the date of issue.

verbs.description: predate (third-person singular simple present predates, present participle predating, simple past and past participle predated)

entries.meaning: To designate a date earlier than the actual one; to move a date, appointment, event, or period of time to an earlier point (contrast "postdate".)
(transitive) To exist or to occur before something else; to antedate.
examples: The Chinese use of Pascal's Triangle predates its discovery by Blaise Pascal.

verbs.description: predate (third-person singular simple present predates, present participle predating, simple past and past participle predated)
